@startuml Workout Sessions - Use Case Diagram

left to right direction

actor "User" as User
actor "System" as System

rectangle "Workout Session Management" {
  usecase "Start Workout Session" as UC1
  usecase "Log Exercise Set" as UC2
  usecase "Complete Session" as UC3
  usecase "Skip Session" as UC4
  usecase "View Session History" as UC5
  usecase "View Session Details" as UC6
  usecase "Track Rest Time" as UC7
  usecase "Add Session Notes" as UC8
  usecase "Delete Session" as UC9
  usecase "Substitute Exercise" as UC10
  usecase "Mark Set as Warmup" as UC11
  usecase "View Live Statistics" as UC12
  usecase "Pause Session" as UC13
  usecase "Resume Session" as UC14

  usecase "Check Personal Records" as UC15
  usecase "Send Notifications" as UC16
  usecase "Track Analytics" as UC17
  usecase "Update Progress Charts" as UC18
}

User --> UC1
User --> UC2
User --> UC3
User --> UC4
User --> UC5
User --> UC6
User --> UC7
User --> UC8
User --> UC9
User --> UC10
User --> UC11
User --> UC12
User --> UC13
User --> UC14

UC1 ..> UC12 : <<include>>
UC2 ..> UC7 : <<include>>
UC2 ..> UC11 : <<extend>>
UC2 ..> UC10 : <<extend>>
UC3 ..> UC8 : <<extend>>
UC4 ..> UC8 : <<include>>

UC3 ..> UC15 : <<include>>
UC3 ..> UC16 : <<include>>
UC3 ..> UC17 : <<include>>
UC3 ..> UC18 : <<include>>

System --> UC15
System --> UC16
System --> UC17
System --> UC18

note right of UC1
  User starts a workout session
  from a planned workout or
  creates an ad-hoc session
end note

note right of UC2
  User logs sets with reps,
  weight, and optional notes
  in real-time during workout
end note

note right of UC3
  Completing session triggers:
  - PR detection
  - Progress updates
  - Notifications
  - Analytics tracking
end note

note right of UC7
  Rest timer countdown between
  sets with audio/haptic alerts
  and option to skip or extend
end note

note right of UC12
  Real-time display of:
  - Total volume lifted
  - Sets completed
  - Duration
  - PRs achieved
end note

@enduml
